description.narrative: The RO remains on-track for the achievement of its 2018-2021 CPIE Programme cycle targets, despite the rise of new emergencies or the worsening of existing ones, particularly in the Central Sahel, the Lake Chad Basin area and in Cameroon. In 2019, in addition to specific activities aimed at strengthening country preparedness and improving sector response capacities, increased attention was given to areas such as better integration of education and protection responses, strengthening the resilience of children affected by protracted crises, and improving care and support for children affected by sexual violence and children affected by armed conflict. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/01/2020
